copy number profiles (CNPs) and calls CNAs. If ploidy is known, FREEC assigns absolute copy number to each predicted CNA. To normalize raw CNPs, the user can provide a control dataset if available; otherwise GC content is used. We demonstrate that for Illumina single-end, mate-pair or paired-end sequencing, GC-contentr normalization provides smooth profiles that can be further segmented and analyzed in order to predict CNAs. Â© The Author(s) 2010. Published by Oxford University Press.","date":"2011-01-01T00:00:00Z","citationCount":172,"authors":[{"name":"Boeva V."},{"name":"Zinovyev A."},{"name":"Bleakley K."},{"name":"Vert J.-P."},{"name":"Janoueix-Lerosey I."},{"name":"Delattre O."},{"name":"Barillot E."}],"journal":"Bioinformatics"}}],"credit":[{"name":"Valentina Boeva","email":"valentina.boeva@inserm.fr","url":null,"orcidid":null,"gridid":null,"rorid":null,"fundrefid":null,"typeEntity":"Person","typeRole":["Primary contact"],"note":null},{"name":"Carino Gurjao","email":"carinogurjao@gmail.com","url":null,"orcidid":null,"gridid":null,"rorid":null,"fundrefid":null,"typeEntity":"Person","typeRole":["Primary contact"],"note":null}],"community":null,"owner":"seqwiki_import","additionDate":"2017-01-13T13:14:38Z","lastUpdate":"2018-12-10T12:58:56Z","editPermission":{"type":"group","authors":["ELIXIR-EE"]},"validated":1,"homepage_status":0,"elixir_badge":0,"confidence_flag":null}